  "market_context": "BTCUSD was in a trading range between ~28500–31000 on the daily chart. Price approached the lower boundary of the range and began forming lower highs, indicating weakening bullish momentum before a downside breakdown.",
  "key_observation": "Before the breakdown, price printed lower highs as it approached the support level (~28500–30000), signaling bearish weakness and increasing likelihood of a downside break.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst applied the LuxAlgo 'Range Detector' indicator to automatically identify the trading range (support at ~28500, resistance at ~31000).",
    "Step 2: The analyst observed that prior to the breakdown, price formed lower highs while approaching the support zone, which is a classic sign of bearish market structure deterioration.",
    "Step 3: The analyst noted the range break occurred when the horizontal support line turned red, confirming the downside breakout from the established range.",
    "Step 4: The analyst emphasized combining the range break signal with price action—specifically the lower highs pattern—to increase confidence in the breakdown."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Lower highs into support within a defined trading range signal weakening demand and increase probability of a downside breakdown; always confirm range breaks with price action structure.",
